"ACRO (Aesthetic and Critical Reasoning Ontology)
is a small ontology for describing how a
professional art critic reasons on a visual work
of art. We have populated it by applying it on the
critical interpretation, carried by Antonello
Negri, of George Grosz's lost artwork "Der
Abenteurer"."
